The error you are seeing is a known bug in the macOS 12.1 SDK headers (specifically NSBundle.h). 
The macro NS_FORMAT_ARGUMENT(1) is incorrectly applied to a method returning NSAttributedString *, 
but the compiler expects it only on methods returning NSString *.

clang -fobjc-arc \
      -framework CoreWLAN \
      -framework Foundation \
      -framework Security \
      -DNS_FORMAT_ARGUMENT\(A\)= \
      wifitool.m -o wifitool

